1. Stack all layers

# Files directory
#################

#Late frost maps
late.frost.dir   = "/Users/consti/Desktop/PhD/Data/Global_layers/Environmental_layers/late_frost_maps/DegreedaysToFrost"
frost.change.dir = "/Users/consti/Desktop/PhD/Data/Global_layers/Environmental_layers/late_frost_maps/TemporalTrends"
last.frost.dir   = "/Users/consti/Desktop/PhD/Data/Global_layers/Environmental_layers/late_frost_maps/LastFrostDate"
frost.prob.dir   = "/Users/consti/Desktop/PhD/Data/Global_layers/Environmental_layers/late_frost_maps/ChangeFrostPropability"

#Covariates
bioclim.dir      = "/Users/consti/Desktop/PhD/Data/Global_layers/Environmental_layers/bioclim_worldclim2"
env.dir          = "/Users/consti/Desktop/PhD/Data/Global_layers/Environmental_layers/environmental_variables"
biome.dir        = "/Users/consti/Desktop/PhD/Data/Global_layers/Ecology_layers/biomes"
sea.dist.dir     = "/Users/consti/Desktop/PhD/Data/Global_layers/Environmental_layers/DistanceToSea"
continents.dir   = "/Users/consti/Desktop/PhD/Data/Global_layers/Environmental_layers/continents"

#Output
output.dir       = "/Users/consti/Desktop/PhD/Publication_material/24) Frost risk/R_data/CompleteRasters"

#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Load raster files
###################

#frost layers
frost.layers.stack   <- stack(list.files(path=paste(late.frost.dir), pattern='*.tif', 
                                         full.names=TRUE))[[c(1:4,17:20)]] # degree-days to last frost
frost.change.stack   <- stack(list.files(path=paste(frost.change.dir), pattern='*.tif', 
                                         full.names=TRUE)) # temporal trends
last.frost.zero      <- mean(stack(list.files(path=paste(last.frost.dir), pattern='*.tif', 
                                              full.names=TRUE))[[59:116]]) # date of last frost below 0C
frost.prob.stack     <- stack(list.files(path=paste(frost.prob.dir), pattern='*.tif', 
                                         full.names=TRUE)) # Probability of frost occurrence in a given year over time

#environmental covariates
bioclim.layers.stack <- stack(list.files(path=paste(bioclim.dir), pattern='*.tif', 
                                         full.names=TRUE)) # bioclim layers
env.layers.stack     <- stack(list.files(path=paste(env.dir), pattern='*.asc', 
                                         full.names=TRUE))[[c(28,33)]] # solar radiation and elevation layer
biome.layer          <- raster(list.files(path=paste(biome.dir), pattern='*.tif', 
                                          full.names=TRUE)) # biome layer
sea.dist.layer       <- raster(paste(sea.dist.dir, "Distance_to_Sea.tif", sep="/"), 
                               pattern='*.tif', full.names=TRUE) # sea distance
continents           <- readShapePoly(paste(continents.dir, "continent.shp", sep="/")) # continents

#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

#rename frost layers
names(frost.layers.stack) = c("Q95_DegreeFiveToFrostFour","Q95_DegreeFiveToFrostZero",
                              "Q95_DegreeZeroToFrostFour","Q95_DegreeZeroToFrostZero",
                              "M_DegreeFiveToFrostFour","M_DegreeFiveToFrostZero",
                              "M_DegreeZeroToFrostFour","M_DegreeZeroToFrostZero") 

names(last.frost.zero) = 'dateLastFrost0C'

#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Aggregate maps
bioclim.layers.stack <- aggregate(bioclim.layers.stack, fact=12, fun=mean) 
env.layers.stack     <- aggregate(env.layers.stack, fact=12, fun=mean)

#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Set boundary of layers
boundary             <- extent(-165, 180, -60, 80)

#crop
frost.layers.stack   <- crop(frost.layers.stack, boundary)
frost.change.stack   <- crop(frost.change.stack, boundary)
last.frost.zero      <- crop(last.frost.zero, boundary)
frost.prob.stack     <- crop(frost.prob.stack, boundary)
bioclim.layers.stack <- crop(bioclim.layers.stack, boundary)
env.layers.stack     <- crop(env.layers.stack, boundary)
biome.layer          <- crop(biome.layer, boundary)
sea.dist.layer       <- crop(sea.dist.layer, boundary)

#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

#Aggregate all layers
complete.layers      <- stack(frost.layers.stack, 
                              frost.change.stack, 
                              last.frost.zero,
                              frost.prob.stack,
                              bioclim.layers.stack, 
                              env.layers.stack, 
                              biome.layer, 
                              sea.dist.layer)

#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

plot(complete.layers[[1]])

# Delete regions with average LSF = 0
complete.layers[complete.layers[[4]] < 0.01]   = NA

#keep only biomes 4,5,6,8 (temperate broadleaf/mixed forest, temperate coniferous forest, boreal forest, temperate grass/shrubland)
complete.layers[complete.layers[[59]] %in% c(1,2,3,7,9,10,11,12,13,14,98,99)] = NA

plot(complete.layers[[1]])

Save complete stack

writeRaster(complete.layers, paste(output.dir, "complete.rasters.grd", sep='/'), overwrite=T)



2. Transform to table

# Extract climate values for all the cases
complete.table = cbind(coordinates(complete.layers), 
                          as.data.frame(complete.layers[[c(1:nlayers(complete.layers))]]))
complete.table = complete.table[complete.cases(complete.table$M_DegreeZeroToFrostZero),]

#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

#Continent intersection
#######################

# coordinates to intersect
coordinates(complete.table) = c("x", "y")
# intersection
complete.table$continent    = over(x=complete.table, y=continents)
# converts the data to dataframe again
complete.table              = as.data.frame(complete.table)

#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# delete Africa 
complete.table = complete.table[complete.cases(complete.table$CONTINENT) & 
                                  complete.table$CONTINENT!="Africa" & 
                                  complete.table$CONTINENT!="Antarctica",]

# split Asia
complete.table$continent_sub <- ifelse(complete.table$CONTINENT=="North America", "North America", 
                                   ifelse(complete.table$CONTINENT=="Europe", "Europe", 
                                         ifelse(complete.table$CONTINENT=="Australia" | 
                                                  complete.table$CONTINENT=="Oceania", "Australia",
                                              ifelse(complete.table$CONTINENT=="South America", "South America",
                                                       ifelse(complete.table$x<80, "West Asia", "East Asia")))))

#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Get new biome column
######################

#get mean LSF per biome
mean_na                 = function (x){mean(x, na.rm=T)}
#get avarage LSF per biome
climate_aggregate_biome = aggregate(complete.table[, 5:6], list(complete.table$WWF_Biomes_HalfDegree), mean_na)
#order new biome column according to average LSF
complete.table$biome    = factor(complete.table$WWF_Biomes_HalfDegree,
                                 levels=climate_aggregate_biome[order(climate_aggregate_biome$Q95_DegreeZeroToFrostZero),]$Group.1,
                                 ordered=T)
#rename
complete.table$biome = gsub(6, "Boreal forest", complete.table$biome)
complete.table$biome = gsub(5, "Conifer forest", complete.table$biome)
complete.table$biome = gsub(4, "Broadleaf/mixed forest", complete.table$biome)
complete.table$biome = gsub(8, "Grass/Shrubland", complete.table$biome)

#delete NAs
complete.table = complete.table[complete.cases(complete.table$biome),]

#delete pixels with warmest month <10C
complete.table <- complete.table[complete.cases(complete.table$wc2.0_bio_2.5m_05) 
                                 & complete.table$wc2.0_bio_2.5m_05>10,]

#check biomes
table(complete.table$biome)
## 
##          Boreal forest Broadleaf/mixed forest         Conifer forest 
##                   9926                   5519                   1889 
##        Grass/Shrubland 
##                   4789
# Get pixel area
################

#create area map
area_map       = raster::area(complete.layers)
plot(area_map, main="Pixel area in km2")

#extract area information
complete.table = data.frame(complete.table, pixelArea=extract(area_map, complete.table[, c("x", "y")]))

Safe table

write.table(complete.table, file=paste(output.dir, "complete.table.csv", sep="/"), 
            col.names=TRUE, row.names=FALSE, quote=FALSE, sep=";")
